Hackity hack ...

Well, I think I got something working on the flight model front.  I
created a flight.so module copying parts out of the other modules to
wrap around the ACM flight model code.  I added the module init
function name to static_modules in fgstatdv.h and probably another
place or two in fgmain.c.  I linked it all together, and everything
seemed to work ... !!!

All the control surface values are hardwired in right now, so there's
not much you can do with it other than watch the numbers scroll across
the screen.  I was dabbling with a little autopilot functionality, but
that's a long way from being useful.  I was just kind of playing
around seeing if I could get any sort of stabalized, controlled
flight.  (It's not immediately obvious how to do this, and my first
several attempts met with a fair amount of frustration.)  However,
after a little tutorial from one of my coworkers on simple control
theory, I think I'm now on the right track.  I at least achieved
very stable flight (although not stabalized on the correct value.)

I created a "modules" directory, and put my stuff under there for now,
but I suppose we should talk about how things should be organized.  My
next step is to see if I can get the ACM hud code going.  I realize
most civilian planes are lacking a hud, but for now it will be useful
for seeing what's going on until we can get panels and scenery going.

Talk to y'all later.

Curt.
