> fgloadc at line 119 to 'dlopen', in fgload.c line 132 to 'dlsym' and 
> again in fgload.c line 312 to 'dlclose'. Then the linker stops.
> Any hint? Did you change the code in any way? Do you have an idea?

Both of these problems should be easy to fix.  Rather than copying
libraries around your system, just add in a "-L/usr/X11R6/lib" before
the "-lX11 -lXext".  The -L directive tells the compiler where it can
go searching for libraries.  Finally add a "-ldl" to the end.  This
will resolve the dlopen dlsym problems.  I've been meaning to send
these changes to Eric ... maybe he can read this and update
makefile.linux. ;-) Here is what that section of the makefile should
look like.

fgmain: $(MAINOBJS)
	gcc $(CFLAGS) -o fgmain $(MAINOBJS) -lm -L/usr/X11R6/lib -lX11 -lXext -ldl

Hopefully this will help you on the Linux front.

Curt.
