Eric,

I am writing to ask you if you would be willing to add an arc
drawing routine to fggrx.[hc]  I need this for the HUD code I'm
working on.

I have some sample code to do this (borrowed again from acm.)  It
looks like in this code, angles are in the range of (0*64 - 359*64).
I think (x,y) is the center of the ellipse.  width and height define
the bounding box of the ellipse.  angle1 and angle2 are the starting
and ending angles for which to draw the arc (or portion of the
ellipse.)  Feel free to munge it up however you like and
flight-gear-ize it.


#define TICKtoRAD(a)    (a * M_PI / (180.0 * 64.0))
#define INCR            (30 * 64)

void VDrawArc (int x, int y, int width, int height, int angle1, 
	       int angle2, int color)
{
        register double w, h, xc, yc;
        register int    incr, x1, x2, y1, y2;

        w = width / 2.0;
        h = height / 2.0;
        xc = x + w;
        yc = y + h;

        if (angle2 < 0) {
                incr = - INCR;
                angle2 = - angle2;
        } else {
                incr = INCR;
	}

        if (angle2 > 360*64) {
                angle2 = 360*64;
	}

        x1 = xc + (w * cos(TICKtoRAD(angle1)));
        y1 = yc - (h * sin(TICKtoRAD(angle1)));

        while (angle2 != 0) {
                angle1 += incr;
                angle2 -= INCR;
                if (angle2 < 0) {
                        angle1 -= angle2;
                        angle2 = 0;
                }
                x2 = xc + (w * cos(TICKtoRAD(angle1)));
                y2 = yc - (h * sin(TICKtoRAD(angle1)));
                DrawLine (x1, y1, x2, y2);
                x1 = x2;
                y1 = y2;
        }
}


Thanks!

Curt.
