Win32 and will eventually support NT, I believe NT4.0 has DirectDraw
support for most video cards, but not Direct3D yet.

I also sent out a message a week or 2 ago concerning a 32-bit graphics lib
developed by Scitech Software (developers of UNIVBE). It is free for
non-commercial use and supports all SVGA modes in a dos extender or Win32
environment. Available for download from www.scitechsoft.com. Look for the
SVGA Kit v6.0.

I have it on my PC, but haven't had the time recently to play with it. It
has libs for Borland and Watcom in addition to MS Visual C++, so there is a
remote possibility it could be ported to other compilers as well.

