  Instead I was able to build a Win16 version which works except for the
  palette stuff.  The executable is in fgwin16.zip.  None of the changes
  should break the Win32 version. (Michael, let me know!)  Unfortunately I
  had to write my own memory management routines.  They are in fgwin16.zip

- I changed a lot of thing that had the type "int" or "FG_INT" to "FG_INT32"
  Some things weren't working well with 16 bit ints.  This will help
  the Macintosh port once I get around to it.

- Michaels makefile for RSXNT is named "makefile.rnt"  I'm still hoping
  to have a working RSXWDK (works with 3.1) version.  (Hasn't happened
  yet.)

- I got some suggestions by mail that haven't gotten put in yet, maybe
  on Thanksgiving :)

