Eric, after downloading the most
recent fgnew.zip with the new
makefile structure I detected that
the makefile.rnt again does not work.

"No rule to make target fgres.res.."

Obviously, grc is again too stupid to
understand your highly developed syntax.
However, a slight correction does the job.

The working makefile.rnt is again appended.

Compiling with DJGPP works well. No need any more
to copy the dll.o manually. Fine.

The palette is definitely different under DOS
and win32, sorry.

Greetings Michael

--------------77251248644C
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii; name="makefile.rnt"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit
Content-Disposition: inline; filename="makefile.rnt"


CC=gcc
FGDEFS=-DRSX
FGLIBS=-lm -lemx -lbsd 
LIBDIRS=-L/rsxnt/lib
SYS_DEFINES=-D__EMX__ -D__GNUC__
CFLAGS= -g -Wall $(FGDEFS) -Zwin32
OBJ_SUFFIX=o
EXECUTABLE=fgmain.exe
EXTRA_OBJS=
RESOURCE=fgres.res
LINK.RESOURCE=rsrc.exe -x -t fgres.res fgmain.exe

.rc.res:
	copy $*.rc $*_c.c
	$(CC) -E $(SYS_DEFINES) $(FGDEFS) -DRC_INVOKED $*_c.c >$*_c.rc
	grc.exe -r fgres_c.rc
	copy fgres_c.res fgres.res
	del $*_c.*


include makefile.inc


